The article commemorates the 55th anniversary of Reverend Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.'s speech during the March for Jobs and Freedom. Dr. King spoke about his dream of equality and justice for all, emphasizing that the United States should treat all people as equals and overcome racial injustices. The article highlights the importance of continuing to create opportunities for all hardworking Americans to achieve the American Dream. It also mentions that the unemployment rate for African Americans has reached a record low. The article concludes by expressing optimism for a shared future as children of God and citizens of the United States, and emphasizes the importance of love and mutual respect.